exports[`mdx preview pipeline > renders the MDX kitchen sink fixture 1`] = `
"<div class="mdx-esm-placeholder" data-line="13">⟨import Hero, { Callout, FeatureGrid as Grid } from "../components/marketing" import * as Charts from "../components/cha…⟩</div>
<h1 data-line="17">MDX Kitchen Sink Fixture</h1>
<p data-line="19">This fixture exercises Markdown mixed with ESM imports, JSX components, inline expressions,
frontmatter, fenced code, and ordinary prose. M5 preview should render the Markdown content,
show imports and exports as compact chips, and replace custom components with placeholder cards.</p>
<div class="mdx-component-card mdx-component-card-flow" data-line="23"><div class="mdx-component-header" data-line="23"><span class="mdx-component-name">Hero</span><code class="mdx-component-props">eyebrow="Native Markdown" title="Plainsong writes MDX without ex…"</code></div></div>
<h2 data-line="25">Markdown Still Works</h2>
<ul data-line="27">
<li data-line="27"><strong>Bold</strong> and <em>italic</em> spans remain ordinary Markdown.</li>
<li data-line="28"><a href="./kitchen-sink.md">Relative Markdown links</a> should stay clickable.</li>
<li data-line="29">Inline math still renders: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">a^2 + b^2 = c^2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.8974em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">a</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.8141em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">b</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.8141em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</li>
<li data-line="30">Emoji shortcodes are typed in source as <code>:sparkles:</code> and completed by M4.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote data-line="32">
<p data-line="32">A blockquote inside an MDX document should preserve its preview styling and source-line anchor.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 data-line="34">JSX Flow Elements</h2>
<div class="mdx-component-card mdx-component-card-flow" data-line="36"><div class="mdx-component-header" data-line="36"><span class="mdx-component-name">Callout</span><code class="mdx-component-props">tone="info" title="Placeholder rendering"</code></div><div class="mdx-component-body" data-line="36"><p data-line="37">Component children may contain <strong>Markdown</strong>, links to <a href="#markdown-still-works">headings</a>, and
inline code. M5 should render the children where safe while keeping the component itself as a
non-executed placeholder card.</p></div></div>
<div class="mdx-component-card mdx-component-card-flow" data-line="42"><div class="mdx-component-header" data-line="42"><span class="mdx-component-name">Grid</span><code class="mdx-component-props">columns={3} items={[ { title: "Fast editing", body…}</code></div></div>
<div class="mdx-component-card mdx-component-card-flow" data-line="51"><div class="mdx-component-header" data-line="51"><span class="mdx-component-name">Charts.LineChart</span><code class="mdx-component-props">dataKey="views" height={240}</code></div></div>
<h2 data-line="53">Inline JSX And Expressions</h2>
<p data-line="55">Inline components like <span class="mdx-component-card mdx-component-card-text"><span class="mdx-component-header"><span class="mdx-component-name">Badge</span><code class="mdx-component-props">tone="success"</code></span><span class="mdx-component-body">Ready</span></span> should become safe inline placeholders.
Expressions such as <code class="mdx-expression-chip">{readingTime}</code> and <code class="mdx-expression-chip">{new Date("2026-06-15").getFullYear()}</code> should render as code chips,
not execute JavaScript.</p>
<p data-line="59">Lowercase HTML can remain real HTML when sanitized:</p>
<div class="note" data-line="61"><p data-line="62"><strong>HTML island:</strong> this should not execute scripts or remote resources.</p></div>
